  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Public Official Responsiveness on Service Delivery at the Sub-national Level</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Compilation of Key research findings and policy recommendations from the DLT project reports into a factsheet 2. Engaging low performing districts to discuss challenges and ways to improve service delivery 3. Roundtable Discussion on the policy options for improving decentralization and local government for improved  service delivery 4. Targeted Stakeholder Engagement with key state actors/agencies on the DLT policy recommendations 5. Working with. 4 Parliamentary Sub-committee in their oversight functions on the sector policy and budget of MDAs 6. Capacity-building training on evidence-based advocacy for media /CSO 7.  Publication of Policy Briefs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x25CF;Improved bureaucratic/local government responsiveness for service delivery recommendations from the DLT
&#x25CF;Parliament (sub-committee on Local Government and Rural Development; Government Assurance; Gender and Children; and Poverty Reduction Strategy) develop strong capacity to provide oversight in the area of service delivery.
&#x25CF;Increased awareness, heightened interest in local government development issues and the use of DLT research findings by media, civil society organizations coalitions/network for advocacy and program intervention.</narrative>
  </description>
